# No em dashes ... prefer ellipses

When **Ryan** (or anyone on this project) is the audience, **never use em dashes** (`—`, Unicode U+2014).

Ryan's voice leans on **ellipses**. When a break could be either ` - ` or `...`, **default to `...`**.

## Use instead

| Situation | Use |
| --- | --- |
| Em dash / clause break (either `-` or `...` works) | **`...`** (preferred) |
| Parenthetical aside | `...` or commas |
| Numeric or label range | `-` without spaces (`$955-968`, `2024-2026`) |
| Compound adjective or slug | hyphen, no spaces (`dual-MHB` only if grammatically needed) |

## Examples

- Bad: `Dual MHB — jackpots only in Mystery Match`
- Good: `Dual MHB ... jackpots only in Mystery Match`
- OK when not a prose break: `Major ~$955-968+ by RTP`

## Scope

Applies to **all assistant-written text**: chat replies, commit messages, PR bodies, docs you draft, guide copy, UI strings, and comments unless Ryan explicitly asks for em dashes.

`AGENT_RULE_NO_EM_DASHES` — searchability token.
